author: jbellis
msg: make empty strings always return the MINIMUM token, and DecoratedKeys containing the MINIMUM token always be considered empty.  This is something we probably should be doing anyway for consistency.  (It was already true for OPP, but not COPP or RP.)
No further special casing should be necessary because we have already abstracted out code that needs to work across multiple partitioners to use IPartitioner.isEmpty, including getRangeSlice.
patch by jbellis; reviewed by Stu Hood for CASSANDRA-745
